Package: python3-pyscstadmin
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Python library and CLI tool for SCST management
 A comprehensive Python library and command-line interface for managing
 SCST (SCSI Target Subsystem for Linux) through the kernel sysfs interface.
 .
 This tool provides complete SCST configuration management with single-pass
 convergence, automatic kernel module loading, and robust error handling.
 .
 Features:
  * Configuration file parsing and validation
  * Complete SCST subsystem configuration
  * Incremental configuration changes
  * Configuration clearing and cleanup
  * Copy manager duplicate LUN handling
  * Comprehensive error handling and logging
 .
 This package includes both the Python library (scstadmin) and the
 command-line tool (pyscstadmin) for SCST administration.